definitions.definition: To create a subclass of (some class).
examples: I subclassed the Button class to create a more specialised FancyButton class for my user interface.

definitions.definition: To cause (an object) to act as an instance of a subclass (by creating the desired subclass and instantiating an object of this subclass).

main_definition: ( transitive , computing ) (in object-oriented programming ) To create a subclass of (some class).
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , computing ) To cause (an object) to act as an instance of a subclass (by creating the desired subclass and instantiating an object of this subclass).
